Nigerian Chamber of Shipping Director-General, Obiageli Obi, a representative of Lloyd’s Maritime Academy United Kingdom, Mr. James Cullen, and Chairman, Shipping and Maritime Security Committee Mr. Mina Oforiokuma, have visited the management of Nigeria Ports Authority (NPA). Discussions on the occasion centred on the domiciliation of foreign based training in the country  to build capacity and enhance skills of our local content in Nigeria’s maritime domain to optimise its productivity and efficiency.